## Steps

1. Click the **Create Mod** button on the Toolbar.

	![](mod_create.png)

1. Select the **Custom Pistol** from hte available mod types.
	
	![](mod_select.png)

	[REGION:tip]
	You can multiselect in this dialog to create multiple assets at the same time. Feel free to add any other weapons, bots, etc. by **Ctrl + Clicking** the assets you want to create in your mod. 
	[/REGION]

1. Enter a name for the mod in the **Name** field. In this case, we've chosen **GrenadeGun**.

	![](mod_name.png)

1. You can enter an **Author** and **Description**, and this data will show in the Mod menu in the game. If you'd like to change this later, you can do so by accessing your mod through the Editor's **Edit -> Plugins** menu.

	![](mod_info.png)

1. Click the **Create Mod** button.

1. Your new mod package will be automatically focused in the **Content Browser**, but it will be at the root level of the mod.

	![image alt text](image_3.png)(w:934 h:288 convert:false)

1. Double click the **Blueprints** folder, then the **Weapons** folder to find the Blueprint asset for your new custom pistol.

	![image alt text](image_4.png)(w:934 h:288 convert:false)

## Results

You now have a mod with a custom pistol that will replace the default pistol in the game. Now it needs the functionality to cause it to explode when thrown.

